      "ESSeqNum": 0,
      "FacilityID": 1000025741,
      "SummaryText": "As a joint venture of Dow Corning, Hemlock Semiconductor, L.L.C. subscribes to and fully supports the American Chemistry Council (ACC) Responsible Care&reg; initiative and the RC 14001 management standard.  Voluntarily participating in these programs is a part of our commitment to improve environmental, health, and safety performance.\n\n\n\nThe Hemlock, Tennessee manufacturing facility has implemented a Risk Management Plan.  The facility maintains communication with the local community officials through its relationship with the LEPC and other activities.\n\n\n\n\n\nAccidental release prevention and emergency response policies\n\n\n\nHemlock Semiconductor, L.L.C. uses policies and procedures to manage environmental, health, and safety performance.  The company has established a Code of Business Conduct to guide its employees.  In addition, the Clarksville facility has implemented safety and environmental management systems.\n\n\n\n\n\nFacility overview and regulated substances\n\n\n\nThe Hemlock, Clarksville facility manufactures silicon based materials for use by solar cell and electronic device manufacturers. The following RMP-regulated chemicals are used in the manufacturing processes: \n\n?    Hydrogen\n\n?    Dichlorosilane\n\n?    Trichlorosilane\n\n.       Hydrogen Chloride (anhydrous)   \n\n\n\n \n\nAccident prevention program\n\n\n\nThe facility uses a systematic approach to prevent accidental releases through employee and contractor programs that include; training, preventive maintenance, policies, procedures, safety reviews, change management procedures, investigations and audits.  \n\nIn addition, the facility has implemented chemical-specific accident prevention measures, including:\n\n?    Use of nitrogen to inert storage tanks\n\n?    Use of high-performance, corrosion-resistant materials\n\n?    Continuous air monitoring at select locations\n\n?    Automated emergency shutdown systems\n\n?    Emergency process scrubbers\n\n\n\n\n\nFive-year accident history\n\n\n\nAs the facility has not begun production, there have been no accidental"
    },
    {
      "ESSeqNum": 1,
      "FacilityID": 1000025741,
      "SummaryText": " releases. The facility has implemented a robust system to insure all accidents are investigated and followed up.\n\n \n\nEmergency response program\n\n\n\nThe Clarksville Facility uses an Incident Command (IC) system for emergency planning and response activities.  The system is based on the National Incident Management System (NIMS) model, modified to fit the facilities organization and operations.  Emergency response plans are coordinated with the Montgomery County Local Emergency Planning Committee and various Montgomery County Emergency Response Agencies. The facility conducts periodic drills to train site and community emergency response personnel, and participates in community-wide drills. \n\n\n\n\n\nPlanned changes to improve safety\n\n\n\nHemlock Semiconductor, L.L.C. strives to continuously improve its environmental, health, and safety performance through management system and equipment reliability improvements.  The facility uses a formalized project-oriented approach to improve performance.\n\n"
    }
